<br>
Other than Dain, I haven't done anything harder that runs around like Brom refers to. I would think a mob that hits for 800+, rampages, fears or knockbacks, and runs around would challange any guild's focus. Think IV with his feet not shackled to the floor and adds- lots of adds.<br>
<br>
Ya, it's kind of neat to see the AoW pushed into the corner and die and it is a testament to a guild's ability. Still there's nothing like standing in a mound of dead raiders and mobs after a half-hour bloodbath. Ah, the screems, the chaos! Kinda nice to see players show that they can do a lot more than CH, make mod rods, and hit the assist key.<br>
<br>
