<br>
Shaman get to slow mobs? We'll yeah, but recently I've taken up meleeing, got my 2HB skill maxed out, currently working on my 1HB skill, and then maybe H2H.<br>
<br>
I also nuke/DoT.<br>
<br>
Yeah, I could just slow the mob and watch the *other* idiot box, but I don't believe in just &quot;doing my job&quot;; I'm there to kill shit as fast as possible. Likewise you'll probably find that the necros are not just twitching and the mages are doing more than summoning modrods. Shaman can get away with it more because we don't have to worry about mana so much, and clerics are pretty much fixed to worrying about CHs, but there's usually some mana to play with somewhere.<br>
<br>
Being a &quot;support class&quot; just means you get more flexibility in what you do. So I don't get crits to watch, but I can tell you that my highest whack with a 2HB went for 96dmg and with procs and whatnot I can normally do 20-30 DPS, not including the odd nuke during enrages. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><DIV align=center>
